# RentFlow frontend environment.
# Copy to `.env` (or `.env.local`) and adjust as needed.

# Backend base URL. Leave unset in local development — the app auto-detects the
# dev machine's LAN IP from the Metro server and targets port 8080.
# Set this for the Android emulator (which can't see the host LAN IP directly),
# a remote/staging server, or web.
#   Android emulator:  EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://10.0.2.2:8080
#   Staging/prod:      EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.rentflow.app
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://10.0.2.2:8080

# Google sign-in. Create OAuth client IDs in Google Cloud console
# (APIs & Services → Credentials). Add the ones you need for your target(s).
# The "Continue with Google" button falls back to a setup message until at least
# one of these is set. Restart Expo with `npx expo start -c` after changing.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_WEB_CLIENT_ID=xxxxxxxx.apps.googleusercontent.com
# EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_ANDROID_CLIENT_ID=xxxxxxxx.apps.googleusercontent.com
# EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_IOS_CLIENT_ID=xxxxxxxx.apps.googleusercontent.com
